- For every additional element, why you are adding it: 
  - Load balancer: To distribute incoming traffic across multiple servers.
  - Extra server: To provide redundancy and handle more traffic.
- Distribution algorithm: Round Robin. It distributes client requests sequentially to each server in the pool, ensuring equal load.
- Active-Active vs Active-Passive: 
  - Active-Active: Both servers handle traffic simultaneously.
  - Active-Passive: One server handles traffic while the other is on standby, taking over only if the primary fails.
- Database Primary-Replica cluster: The Primary node handles all write operations, and data is copied to Replica nodes. Replicas handle read operations to reduce load on the primary.
- Difference between Primary and Replica: Primary handles both reads and writes. Replica is strictly read-only.

Issues:
- SPOF: The Load Balancer is now the Single Point of Failure. If HAProxy dies, no traffic reaches the servers.
- Security issues: There is no firewall to block malicious traffic, and no HTTPS, so traffic is unencrypted and can be intercepted.
- No monitoring: We have no way of knowing if a server crashes or if resources (CPU/RAM) are maxed out until users complain.
